# Step 1 вҖ“ Create the folders

```
CarePlate/
в”Ӯ
в”ңв”Җв”Җ index.html
в”ңв”Җв”Җ css/
в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ style.css
в””в”Җв”Җ js/
    в””в”Җв”Җ app.js
```

---

# Step 2 вҖ“ Move the CSS

Everything between

```html
<style>
```

and

```html
</style>
```

goes into

```css
css/style.css
```

---

Then replace

```html
<style>
    ...
</style>
```

with

```html
<link rel="stylesheet" href="css/style.css">
```

inside `<head>`.

Your `<head>` becomes:

```html
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport"
          content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">

    <title>Care Plate</title>

    <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/style.css">
</head>
```

---

# Step 3 вҖ“ Move the JavaScript

Everything between

```html
<script>
```

and

```html
</script>
```

goes into

```javascript
js/app.js
```

---

Replace it with

```html
<script src="js/app.js"></script>
```

just before `</body>`.

Your page ends like this:

```html
    </main>
</div>

<script src="js/app.js"></script>

</body>
</html>
```

---

# That's it.

The browser treats it exactly the same.

Nothing changes visually.

Nothing breaks.

But editing becomes **much** easier.

